<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT-365 Diesel Engine Diagnostics (2002) - ELECTRONIC CONTROL SYSTEMS DIAGNOSTICS - Pin Point Diagnostics -
        Connector Checks to Ground
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Connector Checks to Ground</title>
        <figure id="f24007" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD31/D31191.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Ground Resistance Check</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>
            <title>Procedure</title>
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect negative battery cable.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use breakout harness to measure resistance from the lead of the harness to the negative
                battery cable.
            </para>
            <randlist type="bullet">
                <item>
                    <para>Sensor signal ground circuits should measure less than 5 ohms.</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>V
                        <subscript>REF</subscript>
                        and signal circuits should measure more than 1k ohms.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>The control side of an actuator will measure more than 1k ohms, but the expected voltage for
                        the other side of the actuator circuit will measure the voltage that the control side was
                        switching, either power or ground.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>If the ECM is switching the ground circuit, the other side of the actuator circuit should
                        measure more than 12 ohms from the connector terminal to battery ground.
                    </para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>If the ECM is switching the power circuit, the other side of the actuator circuit should
                        measure less than 5 ohms from the connector terminal to battery ground.
                    </para>
                </item>
            </randlist>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
